  "text": "• We suggest against using pharmacogenomic testing to determine initial warfarin doses for most patients. Well-managed warfarin therapy reduces the risk of adverse events including recurrent VTE and bleeding and the costs associated with VTE treatment [1] . Common factors linked to non-therapeutic INR results include changes in dietary vitamin K intake, concomitant medications, non-adherence, initiation phase of warfarin therapy, and changes in health status. Unfortunately, no reason can be identified for nearly half of non-therapeutic INRs [CITATION_1] . Suggestions for optimizing warfarin therapy addressing these and other factors are discussed briefly below.",
